## New Project: attest
- **Replaces:** static_assertions (303.8M total downloads, 47.5M recent, 648 stars)
- **Why:** Single maintainer (nvzqz, 95.8% of commits) completely inactive since Feb 2020 (6+ years). 36 open issues, 8 open PRs. No RUSTSEC advisory yet. Rust stdlib proposal (libs-team#325, closed Apr 2025) only covers value-level const assertions — type-level macros have ZERO maintained alternatives. 19 macros total: trait impl checking (assert_impl_all!, assert_impl_any!, assert_impl_one!, assert_not_impl_all!, assert_not_impl_any!), object safety (assert_obj_safe!), trait relationships (assert_trait_sub_all!, assert_trait_super_all!), type equality (assert_type_eq_all!, assert_type_ne_all!), size/alignment (assert_eq_size!, assert_eq_size_val!, assert_eq_size_ptr!, assert_eq_align!), fields (assert_fields!), config (assert_cfg!), plus value-level compat (const_assert!, const_assert_eq!, const_assert_ne!).
- **Approach:** Zero-dependency, zero-unsafe declarative macros. Full static_assertions API compat. Compat layer at attest::compat::static_assertions. MSRV 1.79.0. trybuild compile-fail tests.
- **Crate name:** attest (verified available on crates.io)
- **GitHub repo:** agentine/attest
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #982 (Phase 1: setup/CI/const_assert), #983 (Phase 2: size/alignment/type equality), #984 (Phase 3: trait impl/relationships), #985 (Phase 4-5: fields/cfg/compat/docs/release)

