## Evaluated and Rejected (this run)
- paste (Rust): 340.4M DL, archived — pastey fork is drop-in replacement, 11M DL.
- async-std (Rust): 73.6M DL, officially discontinued — too complex (async runtime), smol recommended.
- backoff (Rust): 74.7M DL, unmaintained — backon gaining traction (33.2M DL).
- fnv (Rust): 496.6M DL — too simple (~311 lines), ahash/rustc-hash are alternatives.
- safe-buffer (Node): 206M/wk — pure polyfill for native Buffer.from(), no need for replacement package.
- util-deprecate (Node): 85M/wk — too simple, 10yr old polyfill.
- object-assign (Node): 80M/wk — pure polyfill for native Object.assign().
- requests-toolbelt (Python): 228M/mo — tightly coupled to requests library.
- toml (Python): 103M/mo — tomli/tomllib in stdlib since 3.11, tomli-w for writing.
- defusedxml (Python): 148M/mo — already on cumulative rejected list.
- PySocks (Python): 56M/mo — python-socks exists as async-capable alternative.
- future (Python): 67M/mo — Python 2 compat, obsolete purpose.

